</div>
<div class='story-column'>
<noscript id='as-https-1516cce5-d7db-a9a6-41b8-4548b49c4b23'>
<div class='story-intro story-content'>

<p>The research paper "ZERZETSEN TORTURE REPORT" provides a blueprint on the illegal use of the "Zerzetsen" no touch torture technique against whistle-blowers and enemies of rogue elements in the establishment elites. <em><strong>The UK&rsquo;s MI5 and MI6 intelligence agencies, Canada&rsquo;s CSIS and the CIA today practice Zerzetsen with impunity</strong></em>. Zerzetsen is a process of character assassination and threats &#8211; its purpose is to poison every aspect of a person&rsquo;s life. Click on this URL to view the recently issued Zerzetsen Torture Report:</p>

<p><a href="http://www.indymedia.org/media/2010/10//942082.doc">http://www.indymedia.org/...</a></p>

<p>Zerzetsen, which means "<em><strong>Oppression by systematic decomposition</strong></em>", is not the old fashioned bloodier medieval form of torture, but a more modern Orwellian 1984 equivalent that was developed by the former GDR Secret Police "The <strong>STASI</strong>" to &nbsp;cause "<em><strong>severe and prolonged suffering</strong></em>" without leaving marks.</p>


</div>
<div class='row'>
<div class='col-sm-12'>
<div id='read-more'></div>
<div class='story-intro-divider'></div>
<div class='story-body story-content'><p><strong>It's just as the STASI treated Dissidents in Former Communist East Germany, except this Human Rights Abuse is happening here today</strong>. The Stasi called it Zerzetsen.</p>

<p>As the paper describes, <em><strong>Zerzetsen starts with character assassination</strong></em> and slander &#8211; It's about manipulating people or groups of people by typical STASI methods (hearsay, gossip, lies, spreading rumours about someone ... the list goes on). Its purpose is to render its victim unemployable and ostracised from his community.</p>

<p><strong>THEN THE THREATS START</strong></p>

<p>Then years of <em><strong>Intimidation, harassment, surveillance, telephone tapping, and death threats</strong></em> follow on. A classic STASI technique - with both oneself and ones children threatened.</p>

<p>As, Gerald R. James, the former Chairman of Astra wrote in reference to his persecution following whistle-blowing that was embarrassing to MI6 and the CIA &#8211; "<em><strong>I was subjected to harassment, burglaries...surveillance, bugging, telephone tapping ... my family suffered considerably ... my brother was killed in an accident never satisfactorily explained</strong></em>"</p>

<p>And then there is <strong>OMERTA</strong> &#8211; a shut down of all forms of help. Zerzetsen is always a crime of the intelligence services; once they are involved people are scared to help. &nbsp;Police, politicians, and human rights agencies &#8211; no exceptions. &nbsp;In the paper there is evidence of a human rights organization being too closely involved with the intelligence services</p>

<p>As the <strong>Boston Center for Refugee Health &amp; Human Rights states</strong> &#8211; "<em><strong>Direct threats to him/her or to a relative are by far the most common form of torture</strong></em>." &nbsp;</p>

<p>The key to "Zerzetsen" is the cover up conspiracy; since without the cover-up, Zerzetsen could never happen. As the Research Paper shows our Politicians, Police are scared of their own intelligence services.</p>

<p><strong>OCCASIONALLY THE PRESS PLUCKS UP THE COURAGE TO REPORT ON ZERZETSEN</strong>.</p>

<p>Under the headline "Lies, Threats and Whistleblowers" journalist Liam Clarke reported in the UK&rsquo;s "Sunday Times" (Oct 2004) how honest police officers were persecuted by MI5. He says - "the Stasi used to call such tactics "<strong>Zerzetsen</strong>", roughly translated as "<em><strong>to undermine, subvert and corrode</strong></em>."&rsquo; He said MI5 have used Zerzetsen "many times before".</p>

<p>On May 31, 2006 Canada&rsquo;s "The Globe and Mail" reported that CSIS has used Zerzetsen, though they call it "D&amp;D" (Diffuse and Disrupt). &nbsp;</p>

<p>Indeed a former Canadian Government "Intelligence Analyst" and whistle-blower has recently (July 2010) written in detail to several journalists confirming that CSIS is still using "D&amp;D" to persecute innocent victims in Canada today. Hopefully the Canadian press will not be too fearful of CSIS to publish his story.</p>

<p><strong>ZERZETSEN - A BLUEPRINT FOR CORPORATE TERRORISM AND A CRISIS FOR DEMOCRACY</strong></p>

<p>The "Zerzetsen" Research Paper is based on a case study of one family&rsquo;s abuse by MI5 / MI6 intelligence services in the UK and CSIS in Canada. D&amp;D, Zerzetsen, Zerzetzen, or Zersetzung -- Call it what you want: It&rsquo;s illegal "no touch torture" whatever you call it. But it&rsquo;s more than just torture!! This override of Rule of Law by the high establishment is symptomatic of a crisis in our Democracy.</p>

<p>The story began years ago in Vancouver, Canada. After I chose to leave Grosvenor International, where I had been their Group Controller, I was character assassinated with lies behind my back. Grosvenor is owned by The Duke of Westminster who, according to the Press, has boasted about his intelligence connections, and is allegedly <strong>Prince Charles</strong>&rsquo;s closest friend.</p>

<p><em><strong>Zerzetsen is not as uncommon as one thinks, and its use by the CIA, MI5, MI6, and CSIS is growing</strong></em>. This report also describes the experience of other innocent victims of Zerzetsen torture by each of these intelligence services &#8211; a Company CEO, an award winning journalist, diplomats, and police officers.</p>

<p>It does seem that our once legitimate Intelligence Agencies are today morphing into a Stasi-style secret police. Not much point in voting for politicians to pass laws, if they don&rsquo;t ensure that these laws are adhered to by government. As this paper shows, the ability of the establishment to <strong>OVERRIDE RULE of LAW and SEIZE-UP our DEMOCRATIC INSTITUTIONS is symptomatic of a crisis in Democracy</strong>.</p>

<p>To view the Research Paper for a blueprint on "Zerzetsen" torture, click on the following URL:</p>

<p><a href="http://www.indymedia.org/media/2010/10//942082.doc">http://www.indymedia.org/...</a></p>

<p>Roderick Russell</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>

